8 An Act relating to crimes and punishments; amending
21 O.S. 2021, Section 1722, as amended by Section
9 255, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (21 O.S. Supp. 2025,
Section 1722), which relates to the taking of crude
10 oil or gasoline; making certain acts unlawful;
providing penalty; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 1722, as
16 amended by Section 255, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (21 O.S. Supp.
17 2025, Section 1722), is amended to read as follows:
18 Section 1722. A. Any person who shall unlawfully take any
19 crude oil or gasoline, or any product thereof, from any pipe,
20 pipeline, tank, tank car, or other receptacle or container and any
21 person who shall unlawfully take or cause to be taken any machinery,
22 drilling mud, pipes, fittings, pumps, and all other equipment or
23 other materials necessary for the drilling or production of oil or
24 gas wells, with intent to deprive the owner or lessee thereof of
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4170 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 said crude oil, gas, gasoline, or any product thereof, machinery,
2 drilling mud, pipes, fittings, pumps, and all other equipment or
3 other materials necessary for the drilling or production of oil or
4 gas wells shall:
5 1. Be guilty of a misdemeanor if the value of said product so
6 taken is less than One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00), and, upon
7 conviction thereof, shall be punished by a fine of not more than
8 Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00), or by imprisonment in the county
9 jail for a term not to exceed sixty (60) days, or by both such fine
10 and imprisonment; and
11 2. Be guilty of a Class C2 felony offense if the value of such
12 product so taken is One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00) or more and,
13 upon conviction thereof, shall be punished by forfeiture of the
14 instrumentality of the crime and by a fine of not less than One
15 Hundred Dollars ($100.00), and not more than Fifty Thousand Dollars
16 ($50,000.00), or by imprisonment in the State Penitentiary custody
17 of the Department of Corrections for a term in the range of one (1)
18 year to ten (10) years, or by both such fine and imprisonment.
19 B. Any person violating the provisions of this section who:
20 1. Takes such product and causes environmental damage to the
21 real property as a direct result of the taking of such product; and
22 2. The direct costs of remediation or restoration of the
23 environmentally damaged real property exceeds the amount of Two
24 Thousand Five Hundred Dollars ($2,500.00),
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4170 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 shal l, upon conviction, be guilty of a felony.
2 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
